    <h2>Expectations</h2><br>
    <h4>Leaders: immiGiving acknowledges that the quest for immigrant rights justice is often married by a lack of helping hands. We want to give leaders, activists, and organizers the platform to enlist assistance on an individual event basis. Whether it be a protest, a panel, or even just a potluck, immiGiving does the outreach for you. As you interact with the immiGiving community we implore our help-seekers to develop skill improvement programs for their volunteers so that they grow within the immigrant rights movement and expand the effectiveness of the immigrant progress.</h4><br>
    <h4>Volunteers: The immigrant community faces many challenges in their daily lives, but they rise above them each time. immiGiving connects individuals who have so much to contribute to grassroots efforts that are working to push for immigrant rights and justice. Through these opportunities, we hope that volunteers make personal connections with other community members who can help develop their leadership skills and knowledge about immigrant right. The only requirement is to fulfill a commitment to its entirety.</h4>
